  "keywords": [],
  "notes": [
    "If you don't have time to season the meat overnight you could refrigerate it for a few hours. The recipe still works well without seasoning the meat in advance, however, the meat will be harder."
  ],
  "overnight": true,
  "slug": "merchants-buckwheat",
  "steps": [
    {
      "name": "",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "Rinse the meat in cold water, dry using paper towels, season with salt, and refrigerate in a sealed container (or wrapped in a film) overnight.",
          "pause": true
        },
        {
          "text": "Rinse the buckwheat, and put it into a bowl, add salt, add water to cover the buckwheat to soften it before cooking.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Prepare the vegetables. **Onion:** cut into small dice. **Carrot:** cut into 1/2 cm half-moons. **Garlic:** cut into thin slices. **Chili:** halve, remove the seeds, and thinly slice.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Cut the meat into 2 cm cubes.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Sauté onion, garlic, and chili on a large frying pan with olive oil and a bit of salt, on medium heat, for 2-3 minutes, until transparent.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add carrots and cook for 3 more minutes.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the meat, and cook until the meat is white on all sides.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add 100 ml boiling water, add 3 bay leaves and a few peppercorns, wait until it boils, reduce the heat, and cook covered for about 30 minutes, until the meat is soft.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the buckwheat (without water).",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add more boiling water, so it’s about 1 cm over the buckwheat. Cook for 10-15 minutes more.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Season with ground black pepper and more salt if needed.",
          "pause": false
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
